examples.en: It was rumoured that Johnson had been poisoned.
Her husband poisoned her drink in order to kill her.
Her childhood had been poisoned by an abusive stepfather.
The soil has been poisoned with chemical waste from the factory.
The mother had poisoned the children's minds against their father.
He was hit with a poisoned dart.
The factory poisoned the air with its fumes.
She poisoned her husband but he did not die.
A postmortem showed that the man had been poisoned.
The rat ravened the poisoned bait just as we had hoped.
His angry outburst poisoned the atmosphere of the party.
Many people consumed the poisoned oil without ill effects.
She was working in a hostile environment poisoned by sexist jokes.
An outstanding fact of our time is that nations poisoned by anti semitism proved less fortunate in regard to their own freedom.
